codex
The flashswap leg in the current verifier is economically inconsistent: it borrows collateral from the pair, then tries to return collateral principal and only a debt-side “fee”, which is not how V2 repayment works. I’m switching that to a pure debt-token repayment path on the same pair, which preserves the finding’s causality and avoids adding extra routes.
